    "This step integrates real-time enhancements into the kernel's codebase.4.",
    "Kernel configuration is then adjusted to activate the real-time features introduced by the PREEMPT RT patch.",
    "This involves selecting appropriate configuration options that enable preemptive capabilities and other realtime functionalities.5.",
    "With the configuration set, the kernel compilation process is initiated, transforming the modified source code into executable kernel binaries.6.",
    "Upon successful compilation, the newly created real-time kernel is installed, replacing or supplementing the existing kernel, thereby introducing realtime capabilities to the system."
